Key Match Events: Liam Livingstone's 87 guided England to a three-wicket win over Australia in the second T20 international.
Jake Fraser-McGurk scored his first international 50 for Australia.
Livingstone was the pick of the England bowlers with 2-16 in his 50th T20 international.
Phil Salt's 39 off 23 deliveries helped England rebuild.
A 90-run partnership off 47 balls between Livingstone and Jacob Bethell swung the game England's way.
Adil Rashid's single saw England over the line with six balls to spare.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia posted a total of 193 for six.
Travis Head scored 31 off 14 balls for Australia.
Josh Inglis contributed 42 off 26 balls for Australia.
Cameron Green and Aaron Hardie hit Sam Curran for 20 off the final over.
